Very nice indeed Solid '82 GD w/ excellent CM sound.

Rockin Roichester Another in a long list of killer Rochester shows. The boys always came here to play.Crispy clean board but it doesn't convey the awesome energy of the magic going on at the War Memorial that night. On fire from the start,the boys tore the roof off.

Trivia question  They opened the doors a little early at this show. you see unlike most venues (post Who concert in Cleveland) Rochester shows at the war memorial were GA.  So the Boys were still on  Stage playing their sound check when the crowd came in. Can anyone Guess what song they were playing ?  i'll give you a hint. They had noit played in for quite awhile and they broke it out later that summer.
